qas.question: What two locations in Florida were renamed after Kennedy by President Johnson?

answers.text: Cape Canaveral and Apollo launch facilities

qas.question: Which two space programs were heavily worked on by President Johnson?

context: As President, Johnson steadfastly pursued the <a1_0>Gemini and Apollo<a1_0/> programs, promoting them as Kennedy's legacy to the American public. One week after Kennedy's death, he issued an executive order renaming the <a0_0>Cape Canaveral and Apollo launch facilities<a0_0/> after Kennedy.
